						<summary>

						<p>On two broken slabs lying in Survey No. 186.</p>						

						<p>The beginning lost. It records the gift of taxes <hi rend="italic">(Kanikās)</hi> collected at the Liṅgālatīrtha by the <hi rend="italic">Reḍḍis</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Karnaṇas</hi> of Gaṅgapērūru to the goddess. Gaṇakalidēvi of Māchupali and other deities for the annual worship. In characters of the 15th century A.D.</p>						

